Features
User Authentication and Authorization: Secure login and role-based access control using Spring Security.
Database Management: Efficient database operations powered by Spring Data JPA and Hibernate ORM.
MVC Architecture: Clean separation of concerns with Spring MVC.
Dynamic UI: Simple and responsive user interface built with Thymeleaf.
Role-Based Functionality: Different user roles (USER, ADMIN, SALES_MANAGER) with specific permissions and views.
Technologies Used
Spring Boot: Core framework for building the application.
Spring Security: Provides authentication and authorization features.
Spring Data JPA: Simplifies database operations.
Hibernate: ORM library for database interactions.
Spring MVC: Facilitates the development of the web layer.
Thymeleaf: Template engine for creating dynamic web pages.
Installation
To set up the project locally, follow these steps:

Clone the Repository:

bash
Копировать код
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/primepicks.git
cd primepicks
Build the Project:

bash
Копировать код
./mvnw clean install
Run the Application:

bash
Копировать код
./mvnw spring-boot:run
Configuration
The application can be configured via the application.properties file located in the src/main/resources directory. Key configurations include:

Database Connection:

properties
Копировать код
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/primepicks
spring.datasource.username=root
spring.datasource.password=yourpassword
Spring Security:
Customize security settings as needed in the SecurityConfig class.

Usage
Once the application is running, you can access it via http://localhost:8080. Depending on your role, you'll have access to different parts of the application:

ROLE_USER: Standard user functionalities like browsing products, adding to cart, and making purchases.
ROLE_ADMIN: Admin functionalities like managing products, viewing user activities, and administrative tasks.
ROLE_SALES_MANAGER: Sales management functionalities including overseeing sales data and managing customer relationships.
User Roles
The application supports three types of users with specific roles:

ROLE_USER: Basic users who can browse and purchase products.
ROLE_ADMIN: Administrators who manage the platform and have the highest level of access.
ROLE_SALES_MANAGER: Users who manage sales operations and customer interactions.
